[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 276 474, with 81 008 cases reported by China. There are now a total of 194 733 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 184 countries/locations outside mainland China representing an increase of 30 168 cases when compared with the data on 19 Mar 2020, with Italy accounting for 5986 of the newly reported cases, Iran for 1237 of newly reported cases, and South Korea for 147 of the newly reported cases. Spain (3433), Germany (4528), France (1617), and the USA (5257) are major contributors to this increase as well. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside of China now represents 70.4% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA is accelerating rapidly as more testing has become available. A global total of 11 417 deaths have been reported, 8162 outside mainland China.

For the 23rd consecutive day, more cases have been reported from outside mainland China than within mainland China. The total number of deaths reported from outside of mainland China is now greater than the total number of deaths reported by mainland China. Mainland China has now gone 3 days without any locally transmitted cases; South Korea has slowly decreased daily new case counts with a significant increase in the past 24 hours. But cases in the USA are escalating very rapidly and Europe's rise is equally daunting. It would be interesting to see an epidemic curve by date of onset to see what the true curve of transmission is as I suspect, now that more testing is being done, many of those tested have been sick for days awaiting testing. - Mod.MPP]

