[2] China: National Health Commission 20 Mar 2020
Date: Fri 20 Mar 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202003/097e6e91ecb6464ea69fd1a324c9b1b4.shtml


At 04:00 on [20 Mar 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 41 new confirmed cases, 7 new deaths (7 in Hubei), and 36 new suspected cases.

On the same day, 590 new cases were cured and discharged, and 1191 people who had been in close contact with known cases and were under medical observation were released. The number of severe cases decreased by 173.

As of 24:00 on [20 Mar 2020], according to reports from 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there were 6013 confirmed cases (among which, 1963 were severe cases), 71 740 were cured and discharged, and 3255 deaths were reported. A total of 81 008 confirmed cases were reported and 106 suspected cases were reported. A total of 685 866 close contacts have been traced and 9371 close contacts are still in medical observation.

There were 0 newly confirmed cases in Hubei (0 in Wuhan), 561 newly cured cases (502 in Wuhan), 7 new deaths (6 in Wuhan), and 5719 confirmed cases (5610 in Wuhan). Among them, 1927 were severe cases (1901 in Wuhan). A total of 58 942 cases of discharged patients were cured (41 891 in Wuhan), 3139 deaths (2504 in Wuhan), and 67 800 confirmed cases (50 005 in Wuhan). There were 0 new suspected cases (0 in Wuhan) and 0 existing suspected cases (0 in Wuhan).

At 04:00 on [20 Mar 2020], 41 newly diagnosed imported cases were reported (14 in Beijing, 9 in Shanghai, 7 in Guangdong, 4 in Fujian, 2 in Zhejiang, Shandong, and Shaanxi, and 1 in Sichuan). As of 24:00 on [20 Mar 2020], a total of 269 confirmed imported cases were reported related to overseas travel.

A total of 408 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan: 256 cases in Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (98 cases discharged, 4 deaths), 17 cases in Macau Special Administrative Region (10 cases discharged), 135 cases in Taiwan (28 cases discharged, 2 deaths) ).

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[The big news, this is now day 3 with no newly confirmed, locally acquired cases in China in the past 24 hours. While 3 days isn't a definitive interruption of transmission it certainly is a very promising early trend. The challenge will be to identify all imported infections before they can escape from detection and start spreading in the community.

According to the report above, a total of 81 008 cases of confirmed COVID-19 have now been reported from mainland China, representing an increase of 41 cases in the past 24 hours since yesterday's (19 Mar 2020) report was prepared. In addition, 7 deaths were reported, all of them by Hubei province. 48 new cases were reported from Hong Kong, which bears watching as the cases have been slowly but steadily climbing. Macau reported no additional newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours.

All 41 newly confirmed cases were imported cases into China representing 100% of all reported cases in the past 24 hours. Cases were reported by Guangdong (7), Beijing (14), Shanghai (9), Fujian (4), 2 each in Zhejiang, Shandong, and Shaanxi, and 1 in Sichuan, bringing the total number of imported cases to 269.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7121173,155 - Mod.MPP]

