C. Iran: 19 644 cases, 1433 deaths
Date: Fri 20 Mar 2020
Source: Daily Nation, Agence France-Presse (AFP) report [edited]
https://www.nation.co.ke/news/world/Irans-coronavirus-death-toll-rises-to-1433/1068-5498370-cgi8a8z/index.html


Iran said Friday [20 Mar r2020] that coronavirus has killed 149 more people in the Islamic republic, raising the country's official death toll from the disease to 1433. Deputy Health Minister Alireza Raisi said 1237 more cases have been confirmed over the past 24 hours and 19 644 people are now known to have been infected in Iran, one of the world's worst-hit countries.

The latest figures come as Iranians celebrate Nowruz, the Persian New Year [20 Mar 2020] which ushers in a 2-week holiday during which Iran's roads are normally filled with people visiting family. The authorities had urged the public to avoid family visits or days out this year to stem the spread of the coronavirus. But footage aired by state television showed hundreds of vehicles pouring out of Tehran on Thursday evening [19 Mar 2020].

Remote sensors installed at tollbooths checked the body temperatures of motorists and their passengers, but there was no mass stay-home as called for by the authorities.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the 24 hours from 19 to 20 Mar 2020, the number of cases of COVID-19 confirmed in Iran grew from 18 407 to 19 644 an increase of 1237 newly confirmed cases. The number of deaths has also increased from 1284 to 1433, an increase of 149 deaths in the 24 hour period. The number of cases continues to grow at an alarming rate, with reports of deaths of many notable figures in the country and of international fame. This seems to be a repetitive story, countries' health sectors being overwhelmed with the pandemic. Wuhan China began, followed by Italy, and now Iran.

The disturbing news is the significant translocation of the population, which unfortunately may lead to continued intra country/provincial exportations of the virus.

A map of Iran showing provinces can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/iran/iran-political-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7121173,128. - Mod.MPP]

